CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 12, 1956, pg. A20, reads: "Bal Masque Winners - Mrs. Dorothy Conrad, Omega Wives representative, left, won first prize in headdress contest at the Urban League Guild's Bal Masque.  Second prize winner, next in line, Mrs. Edna Stewart, of The Pittsburghers.  Ethel Littlejohn and Margaret Driesdale show the headdress which won them first and second prizes in general competition. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Dorothy Conrad, Edna Stewart, Ethel Littlejohn, and Margaret Driesdale, posed in elaborate hats for headdress contest at the Urban League Guild's Bal Masque, William Penn Hotel
